                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You can turn on short_tags in your php.ini, apache configuration, or .htaccess file. In your php.ini, use the following:\n{code}\nshort_open_tag = On\n{code}\nWithin your apache configuration or .htaccess, use the following:\n{code}\nphp_flag short_open_tag On\n{code}\n\nRegardless, you can also always use long tags: \"<?php\" and \"<?php echo\" will *always* work, even in your phtml files.",
